{
  "stem": "11272.2",
  "chunk_idx": 8,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 2.9,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "As a result, they couldn't shoot our planes down, the Allied planes down.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "But they found out, so they used to come in and just take two or three guys every day and shoot them or torture, cut an arm off.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "Another time, a group of SS men came into our section there, where our barrack was, and ordered two boys to pick up a boy and throw him up.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And they used to put the bayonet on the gun and see how deep the bayonet would go into the boy.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "Or another group used to come in, and they bet whether he's going to shoot the left or right eye out of a young boy.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "And there was also a-- similar to Ilse Koch.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "She used to come in and make us stand out in the cold winter so she could check the tattoos, what color skin we have so she would pick what color she wanted to make lamp shades out of.",
      "word_count": 39
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "And the SS men used to order the arm to be whacked off.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "It's very difficult to describe.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "But what is more even difficult is that everybody else of the Germans and the civilians just stood by watching, didn't care-- I mean, didn't care at all.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "That was even more painful than the vicious things that these guards used to do.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "The only time I experienced that was when they evacuated us from the camp, and one of the Hungarian guards turned to the other Hungarian guards, and he says, we are going to be captured anyway.",
      "word_count": 36
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "The Germans are going to lose the war.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And he put his gun to his mouth, and he blew his brains out.",
      "word_count": 14
    }
  ],
